HEADWORD: Footfall
<hw>Foot"fall`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A setting down of
the foot; a footstep; the sound of a footstep.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Seraphim, whose <qex>footfalls</qex> tinkled on the tufted
floor.</q> <rj><qau>Poe.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Footfight</ent>⟦br⟧
